<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-649  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 649.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Nov 1990 v15 n12 p272(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Magnetic vs optical. (magnetic storage or optical storage)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tazelaar, Jane Morrill.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>In the data storage debate over optical and magnetic media anumber of different innovative technologies exist.andP;  On the opticalside, using light to store data in crystals, and the new 'phasechange' techniques for optical disks are just two technologicalbreakthroughs.andP;  The future of disk drives depends upon thedevelopment of speed, densities, capacity, and recording means andmaterials.andP;  Solid-state semiconductor technology is another newmedia for disk storage, along with credit-card sized flash memoryintegrated circuits.andP;  The use of digital audio tape and other tapemedia are becoming increasingly important for backing up assystems become larger.andP;  To enhance storage space in both opticaland magnetic media, data compression techniques are now the normrather than the exception.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Storage MediaFuture TechnologiesOptical Memory.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>